SIMPLE: island
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Island
<hw>Is"land</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>iland</ets>,
<ets>yland</ets>, AS. <ets>⟦imac⟧gland</ets>, <ets><?/gland</ets>,
<ets><?/glond</ets>; <ets>⟦imac⟧g</ets>, <ets><?/g</ets>, island +
<ets>land</ets>, <ets>lond</ets>, land. AS. <ets>⟦imac⟧g</ets>,
<ets><?/g</ets>, is akin to AS. <ets>e⟦aacute⟧</ets> water, river, OHG.
<ets><?/uwa</ets>, G. <ets>au</ets> meadow, Icel. <ets>ey</ets> island,
Dan. & Sw. <ets>⟦oum⟧</ets>, Goth. <ets>ahwa</ets> a stream, water, L.
<ets>aqua</ets> water. The <it>s</it> is due to confusion with
<ets>isle</ets>. Cf. <er>Ait</er>, <er>Eyot</er>, <er>Ewer</er>,
<er>Aquatic</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A tract of land surrounded by water, and smaller
than a continent. Cf. <er>Continent</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything regarded as resembling an island; <as>as,
an <ex>island</ex> of ice</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>See <er>Isle</er>, <pos>n.</pos>,
2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Islands of the blessed</b></col> <fld>(Myth.)</fld>,
<cd>islands supposed to lie in the Western Ocean, where the favorites of
the gods are conveyed at death, and dwell in everlasting
joy.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Island</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Island
<hw>Is"land</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
cause to become or to resemble an island; to make an island or islands
of; to isle.</def> <rj><au>Shelley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To furnish with an island or with islands; <as>as,
to <ex>island</ex> the deep</as>.</def> <rj><au>Southey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Islander</ent>⟦br⟧
